methods.execHappened:
A new execution happened using this row data.

:param data: (ExecPrioritizer.DATATYPE) - data used in the execution.
methods.priority:
Compute the priority for processing the data at the indicated table rowSet.

:param dataManager: (ExecPrioritizer.ROWDATAMANAGERTYPE) - interface for accessing and querying data contained in rows of a dynamic table.
:param index: (long) - rowSet of the data in the fit data manager source table.
:return: (int) priority of processing the data at the indicated rowSet. Higher numbers are higher priority.

text: An interface for prioritizing the execution of table rows.
